#  clap-builder distinctive features:
#    - FLUENT BUILDER ‚Äî `Command::new(name).about().version().
#      arg().subcommand().get_matches()` chained method calls
#      construct the CLI at RUNTIME (not compile time)
#    - `Command` type ‚Äî represents a CLI (top-level or subcommand);
#      `Command::new(name)` constructor + `.about()` / `.version()`
#      / `.author()` / `.long_about()` metadata methods
#    - `Arg` type ‚Äî represents a flag or positional; `Arg::new
#      (name)` + `.short(char)` / `.long(name)` / `.help(text)` /
#      `.default_value(val)` / `.required(bool)` / `.action
#      (ArgAction::X)` / `.value_parser(parser)` / `.num_args
#      (range)` chaining
#    - `ArgAction` enum ‚Äî controls flag behavior: `SetTrue` /
#      `SetFalse` (boolean flag), `Set` (value-bearing), `Append`
#      (repeatable accumulating), `Count` (occurrence counter
#      for -v/-vv/-vvv), `Help` / `Version` (auto-trigger)
#    - `ArgMatches` query API ‚Äî `.get_one::<T>(name)` / `.get_many
#      ::<T>(name)` / `.get_flag(name)` / `.get_count(name)` to
#      retrieve parsed values from the matches struct
