#      subcommand is itself a `Command` instance; matches via
#      `matches.subcommand()` returning `Option<(&str,
#      &ArgMatches)>`
#    - `subcommand_required(true)` / `arg_required_else_help
#      (true)` ‚Äî auto-show help if no subcommand/args provided
#    - DYNAMIC CONSTRUCTION ‚Äî `.subcommand()` can be called in
#      a loop with subcommands discovered at runtime (e.g.
#      plugin systems where subcommands are loaded from
#      configuration files or shared libraries)
