#  Usage:
#    hvm <subcommand> [subcommand-options] <file>
#
#  Subcommands:
#    run <FILE>                     Interprets a file (using
#                                   pure Rust interpreter ‚Äî most
#                                   portable but slowest single-
#                                   threaded)
#    run-c <FILE> [--io]            Interprets a file (using
#                                   compiled C runtime ‚Äî faster
#                                   single-threaded; --io enables
#                                   IO operations)
#    run-cu <FILE> [--io]           Interprets a file (using
#                                   CUDA GPU runtime ‚Äî massive
#                                   parallel speedup on NVIDIA
#                                   GPUs; --io enables IO)
#    gen-c <FILE> [--io]            Compiles a file to a STANDALONE
#                                   C source file (compile with
#                                   any C compiler to get a
#                                   self-contained binary; --io
#                                   includes IO support in the
#                                   generated binary)
#    gen-cu <FILE> [--io]           Compiles a file to a STANDALONE
#                                   CUDA source file (compile
#                                   with NVCC for a CUDA-enabled
#                                   binary; --io includes IO)
#
#  Subcommand-specific options:
#    --io                           (run-c, run-cu, gen-c, gen-cu
#                                   only) Enable IO operations
#                                   (file I/O, network, etc.) in
#                                   the runtime / generated code.
#                                   Default: pure functional
#                                   evaluation with no side
#                                   effects.
#
#  Common positional:
#    <FILE>                         HVM bytecode source file (.hvm
#                                   or .hvm2 extension by
#                                   convention; ASCII text
#                                   representation of HVM
#                                   interaction-net programs)
#
#  Auto-generated by clap:
#    -h, --help                     Show help
#    -V, --version                  Show HVM version
#
#  Examples:
#    hvm run program.hvm                     # Rust interpreter
#    hvm run-c program.hvm                   # C runtime
#    hvm run-c --io program.hvm              # C runtime with IO
#    hvm run-cu program.hvm                  # CUDA GPU runtime
#    hvm run-cu --io program.hvm             # CUDA with IO
#    hvm gen-c program.hvm > program.c       # Generate C source
#    hvm gen-c --io program.hvm > program.c  # Generate C with IO
#    hvm gen-cu program.hvm > program.cu     # Generate CUDA source
#    hvm --help                              # Show help
#    hvm --version                           # Show version
#    hvm run --help                          # Subcommand help
